description:
Astro Boy has been badly banged up and there's no one else to stop Deadcross's dastardly plans! Can Mustachio rescue Astro Boy? Even if he can, how will anyone be able to fix him in time to stop Deadcross from forcing President Rag to resign?! Also included are Buddha, Dororo, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: His Highness Deadcross Chapter Four
  • Buddha Part Two: The Four Encounters Chapter Two
  • Dororo: The Fair Fudo Chapter One
  • Black Jack: The Blind Acupuncturist
name: Vol. 26

description:
The world famous magician Kino is in town for a show, and Astro and friends are lucky enough to find themselves in the audience! At their side is the "God of Manga" himself, Osamu Tezuka, who gives readers a crash course on cartoon techniques! Also included are Buddha, Phoenix: Dawn, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Third Magician Chapter One
  • Buddha Part Two: Rahula Chapter One
  • Phoenix: Dawn Chapter Two
  • Black Jack: Disowned Son
name: Vol. 27

description:
In Black Jack, an incredibly strange disease is afflicting the African village Black Jack has been called to help... The people and animals are shrinking! And not just a little bit. Anyone infected slowly shrinks down to a fraction of their normal size, and even elephants become small enough to fit in your hand. Unfortunately, getting smaller doesn't seem healthy: once an organism shrinks below one-third its size, it tends to die. And the worst part is-- Not only is there no cure, but Black Jack is infected too! Can he find a way to fix this before he shrinks into oblivion? Also included are Astro Boy: The Third Magician, Buddha, and Adolf.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Third Magician Chapter Two
  • Buddha Part Two: Rahula Chapter Two
  • Adolf: An Exile In Japan Chapter Three
  • Black Jack: Shrinking
name: Vol. 28

description:
The demonic Fudo's anger surges as it tries to take Dororo's face for itself, but a well timed reunion between Dororo and Hyakkimaru foils the creature's plot! Pride still drives the two boys apart, and they'll have to set aside their differences if they want to slay Hyakkimaru's 19th demon. Later, a chance bathtime discovery points towards a fantastic treasure and another sliver of Dororo's past...! Also included are three more adventures with Astro Boy, Buddha, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Third Magician Chapter Three
  • Buddha Part Two: The Five Ascetics Chapter One
  • Dororo: The Fair Fudo Chapter Two
  • Black Jack: Dingoes
name: Vol. 29

description:
On the tiny island of Aragashima, an amazing theme park rises up from the ocean: Robotland! Here the creations of Dr. Haido, fashioned after the fairy tale characters of old, bring stories and legends from around the globe to life. Still, Astro Boy isn't enchanted by Robotland - must his fellow creations live as playthings for humans? Find out in the first chapter of Astro Boy: Robotland! Also included are Buddha, Phoenix: Dawn, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Robot Land Chapter One
  • Buddha Part Two: The Five Ascetics Chapter Two
  • Phoenix: Dawn Chapter Three
  • Black Jack: Your Mistake!
name: Vol. 30

description:
In this issue's Black Jack, money keeps mysteriously appearing! Pinoko has been meticulously collecting it, but neither she nor the doctor can figure out where it's coming from, at first. After collecting quite a sum and devising a plan to find out who is leaving these unexpected presents, Black Jack is baffled to find that the one dropping off bills and coins anonymously is... a little bird?! What could a bird be doing with money, anyway? Join Black Jack and his assistant Pinoko as they try to figure out their feathered friend's motivations. Also included are Astro Boy: Robot Land, Buddha, and Adolf.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Robot Land Chapter Two
  • Buddha Part Two: Dawn of the Journey
  • Adolf: An Exile In Japan Chapter Four
  • Black Jack: The Robin and the Boy
name: Vol. 31

description:
In Black Jack: The Boy Who Came From the Sky, a father will stop at nothing to get his dying son help from the most skilled doctor in the world, Black Jack himself. But when he has to defect from his nation and commit treason to do it, Black Jack doesn't want a foreign nation's armed forces to see him as someone harboring a fugitive! As complications arise, the boy's life is in danger, but can Black Jack help him without getting himself in terrible trouble too? Can Black Jack help him at all? Also included in this issue are Astro Boy: Robot Land, Buddha, and Dororo.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Robot Land Chapter Three
  • Buddha Part Two: The Death of Bandaka Chapter One
  • Dororo: Sebame
  • Black Jack The Boy Who Came From the Sky
name: Vol. 32

description:
This issue introduces a new Astro Boy story: Ivan the Fool! Astro Boy gets a summer job as a steward aboard a huge space cruiser, but what will he find when the ship crashes and he's forced to flee from the wreckage to the unknown surface of the moon? The ship's remaining passengers and Astro Boy find a strange new world waiting for them! Also included are Buddha, Phoenix: Dawn, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Ivan the Fool Chapter One
  • Buddha Part Two: The Death of Bandaka Chapter Two
  • Phoenix: Dawn Chapter Four
  • Black Jack: Black Jack In Hospital
name: Vol. 33

description:
In Astro Boy: Ivan the Fool, Astro Boy discovers the truth behind the huge monster that seems to be rampaging around the moon, and it's far different from what he expected! As it turns out, other people have been to the far side of the moon before him! Also included are Buddha, Adolf, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Ivan the Fool Chapter Two
  • Buddha Part Three: The Ordeals
  • Adolf: An Exile In Japan Chapter Five
  • Black Jack: A Woman's Case
name: Vol. 34

description:
In Astro Boy: A Day to Remember, a three day celebration has begun in which families ask robots to play the roles of the dearly departed. Astro volunteers for a mourning couple to act as Jiro, a young son that mysteriously disappeared. The mystery deepens when Astro finds an odd machine in Jiroís room and gangsters start showing upÖ! Also included are Buddha, Dororo, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: A Day To Remember
  • Buddha Part Three: Survival of the Fittest Chapter One
  • Dororo: Hell Screen
  • Black Jack: Two Dark Doctors
name: Vol. 35

description:
In Black Jack: The Residents trouble is brewing in the operating room! Three residential doctors are at odds with their boss and beg Black Jack to help them operate on a young boy. After offering the doctor a paltry fee, Black Jack rejects the offer and leaves them to their own devices. But what happens when their inaccurate diagnosis proves deadlyÖ? Included are Astro Boy, Buddha, and Phoenix.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Ghost Manufacturing Machine Chapter One
  • Buddha Part Three: Survival of the Fittest Chapter Two
  • Phoenix: Dawn Chapter Five
  • Black Jack: The Residents
name: Vol. 36

description:
Black Jack: Recollections of a Spinster raises the question... do doctors control their patient's fate? Mary, a nurse, witnesses the death of a dear friend while in the operating room! As Mary questions her worth in the medical field, she comes across a collapsed pregnant woman in need of an emergency operation. However, no doctors are available on such short notice and the only option is the infamous Black Jack! Whatís a nurse to do?! Also included are Astro Boy, Buddha, and Adolf.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Ghost Manufacturing Machine Chapter Two
  • Buddha Part Three: The Hag and the Waif Chapter One
  • Adolf: An Exile In Japan Chapter Six
  • Black Jack: Recollections of A Spinster
name: Vol. 37

description:
In Buddha: The Hag and the Waif, Devadatta escapes the clutches of his captors and flees into the city. Unable to tell friend from foe, the wolf-boy falls into the devious care of the hag Ghagra, who sees murderous potential in little Devadatta. What will the wolf-boy decide as heís groomed for the hagís desire for revenge? Also included are Astro Boy, Dororo,and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Ghost Manufacturing Machine Chapter Three
  • Buddha Part Three: The Hag and the Waif Chapter Two
  • Dororo: The Two Sharks
  • Black Jack: Pinoko Loves You
name: Vol. 38

description:
In Buddha: The Hag and the Waif Chapter 3, Ghagra furiously punishes Devadatta for his failed assassination and goes on a wanton spending spree! However, it doesnít last long, and the hagís jealously spins out of control, sending Devadatta to infiltrate and murder a member of a wealthy family! But what happens when the lady of the house is one step ahead of the devious Ghagra? Also included are Astro Boy, Phoenix, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Ghost Manufacturing Machine Chapter Four
  • Buddha Part Three: The Hag and the Waif Chapter Three
  • Phoenix: Dawn Chapter Six
  • Black Jack: Tenacity
name: Vol. 39

description:
In Black Jack, two men stumble into the doctor's clinic begging him to save them. One of them suffers from multiple bullet wounds; the other has broken legs. They don't seem to know each other, but they're actually connected, and the nature of this connection might pose complications for patients and doctor alike! Also included are Astro Boy: Crucifix Island, Buddha Part Three, and Adolf.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Crucifix Island Chapter One
  • Buddha Part Three: Sukanda the Knigh Chapter One
  • Adolf: An Exile In Japan Chapter Seven
  • Black Jack: An Odd Relationship
name: Vol. 40

description:
In Black Jack: Baby Blues, Maggie, a delinquent, finds an abandoned baby in a storage locker! She leaves it to die, only to realize that perhaps she and the infant have more in common than she thinks. As the babyís condition worsens and the threat of death looms, Maggie can only think of one infamous doctor that can save the day! This issue also includes Astro Boy, Buddha, and Dororo.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Crucifix Island Chapter Two
  • Buddha Part Three: Sukanda the Knigh Chapter Two
  • Dororo: Shiranui
  • Black Jack: Baby Blues
name: Vol. 41

description:
In Black Jack: False Image, Black Jack attends an elementary school reunion! Former classmates from far and wide attend, but the biggest guest of honor is out sick: the beloved teacher Mr. Shima. Black Jack is tasked with finding the reclusive man, but what plagues Shima is not illness, but addiction. Can Shima recover in time for a reunion with his former students? Also included are Astro Boy, Buddha, and Phoenix.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Crucifix Island Chapter Three
  • Buddha Part Three: Sukanda the Knigh Chapter Three
  • Phoenix: Dawn Chapter Seven
  • Black Jack: False Image
name: Vol. 42

description:
In Buddha: Nterview at Mt. Pandava, the brothers Dhepa and Assaji live a simple existence in the mountains, but they soon discover that Assaji has a talent for something far grander than they: the ability to see the future. Assajiís feats soon reach the ears of a king, who summons them to test their mettle, only to have his own death predicted! Will the king take this prophecy as insult or advice...? Also included are Astro Boy, Adolf, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Crucifix Island Chapter Four
  • Buddha Part Three: Interview At Mt. Pandava Chapter One
  • Adolf: An Exile In Japan Chapter Eight
  • Black Jack: The Scream
name: Vol. 43

description:
In Astro Boy: Space Snow Leopard, Tezuka does his take on the ìangel hairî snow phenomena! One snowy day, Astro discovers all the robots in the city completely drained of energy and rushes to investigate. Surprisingly, his search leads him to a crazed man and his mysterious "space snow leopard!î Is the leopard responsible for the robotsí mass collapse? And why exactly isn't Astro affected?! Also included are Buddha, Dororo, and Black Jack!

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Space Snow Leopard Chapter One
  • Buddha Part Three: Interview At Mt. Pandava Chapter Two
  • Dororo: The Cruel Cape
  • Black Jack: Drifter In A Ghost Town
name: Vol. 44

description:
In Black Jack: Pinoko Love Story, Pinoko gets a boyfriend! When heís brought in with excruciating abdominal pain, Black Jack makes a terrifying discoveryóthe boyís insides are inverted! This topsy turvy mystery is one that even Black Jack struggles to solve, but the key may lie with the most unlikely person: Pinoko! Also included are Astro Boy, Buddha, and Phoenix.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Space Snow Leopard Chapter Two
  • Buddha Part Three: In the Forest of Trials Chapter One
  • Phoenix: Dawn Chapter Eight
  • Black Jack: Pinoko Love Story
name: Vol. 45

description:
In Black Jack: The Sewer Way, a terrorist organization botches a bombing leaving their leader fatally injured in the sewers. His lackeys track down Black Jack, but the doctor refusesÖat first! Just what is up Black Jackís sleeve? Also included are Astro Boy, Buddha, and Adolf!

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Artificial Sun Chapter One
  • Buddha Part Three: In the Forest of Trials Chapter Two
  • Adolf: The Half-Aryan Chapter One
  • Black Jack The Sewer Way
name: Vol. 46

description:
The second installment of Astro Boy: The Artificial Sun continues! The professor reveals an abandoned project that could change the worldÖ except it already has! Someone has hijacked the project to melt the world into a new climate and the only one who can stop them is Professor Ochanomizu! Also included are Buddha, Dororo, and Black Jack!

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Artifical Sun Chapter Two
  • Buddha Part Three: In the Forest of Trials Chapter Three
  • Dororo: Midoro
  • Black Jack: The Sea Smells of Romance
name: Vol. 47

description:
Astro Boy: The Artificial Sun concludes in this heated finale! Astro Boy returns and teams up with the human-turned-robot Holmspun! Will they be able to stop the rogue sun from frying the earth? Or with they crash and burn? Also included are Buddha, Pheonix, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Artifical Sun Chapter Three
  • Buddha Part Three: In the Forest of Trials Chapter Four
  • Phoenix: Future Chapter One
  • Black Jack: Tetsu of the Yamanote Line
name: Vol. 48

description:
In Black Jack: Titles, Black Jack faces his strangest situation yet! A foreign minister makes an odd requestócan he sit and watch Black Jack work during a surgery at a hospital? The doctor accepts, but territorial surgeons drive him out of the operating room! What happens when Black Jack canít make good with a foreign ministerís request? Also included are Astro Boy, Buddha, and Adolf.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Beginning of the Contradiction
  • Buddha Part Three: In the Forest of Trials Chapter Five
  • Adolf: The Half-Aryan Chapter Two
  • Black Jack: Titles
name: Vol. 49

description:
In Black Jack: Lost and Found, a loving husband sacrifices all to save his dying wife. After months of scraping enough to pay Black Jackís thirty million yen fee, the check is lost on its way to the doctor! Desperate, the husband offers anything in exchange for the surgery! But just what does Black Jack have in mind? Also included are Astro Boy, Buddha, and Dororo!

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Living On Earth, 101
  • Buddha Part Three: Chastised
  • Dororo: Donburi Belly
  • Black Jack: Lost and Found
name: Vol. 50

description:
The time has come for Assajiís self-prophesied death in Buddha: Assajiís End! Even as time runs out, Assaji still offers predictions for all who approach, including a princess that will have her love, but only for one night. As the evening draws nearer, Siddhartha is determined to change his tiny friendís fate, but can he? Also included are Astro Boy, Phoenix, and Black Jack!

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Birth of Neva #2
  • Buddha Part Three: Assaji's End
  • Phoenix: Future Chapter Two
  • Black Jack: Burned Doll
name: Vol. 51

description:
The tragedy continues in Buddha: Part Three, Sujata! Horrified and inspired by Assajiís piety, Siddhartha embarks on an intense journey of suffering. But as the days pass, Siddhartha begins hearing a mysterious voice. Is he reaching enlightenment or is he simply going mad? Also included are Astro Boy, Adolf, and Black Jack!

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Baro, The Robot
  • Buddha Part Three: Sujata Chapter One
  • Adolf: The Half-Aryan Chapter Three
  • Black Jack: The Heart of A Giant
name: Vol. 52

description:
There's peril afoot in Black Jack: Gas! It seems like just an ordinary day as Pinoko does her chores, including taking the medicine she needs to nurse her oncoming cold... When, suddenly, Black Jack frantically tells her the pill she took was none other than potassium cyanide! The doctor has less than an hour to save Pinoko! Can he beat the odds? Also included are Astro Boy, Buddha, and Dororo!

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy Scara Disappears
  • Buddha Part Three: Sujata Chapter Two
  • Dororo: The Four-Turned Bonze
  • Black Jack: Gas
name: Vol. 53

description:
In Buddha: Part Three, The Crystal Prince, Siddhartha finds out his home town was massacred by the country of Kosola! Siddharthaís parents are now in the hands of King Prasenajit and their fates are unknown. The messenger of the news, Dhepa, smugly reminds the ascetic that he can no longer have attachments to this world. Can the now distraught Siddhartha truly achieve enlightenment? Also included are Astro Boy, Phoenix, and Black Jack!

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Energy Tube Chapter One
  • Buddha Part Three: The Crystal Prince Chapter One
  • Phoenix: Future Chapter Three
  • Black Jack: From Afar
name: Vol. 54

description:
Pinoko gets a pet dog in Black Jack: Thieving Dog! The scruffy mongrel, Largo, is injured severely, but Pinoko strong-arms Black Jack into saving her! Unfortunately, Largo has an odd habit of kleptomania, causing more harm than good for the doctor. Is this dog simply a thief or is there a method to her madness? Also included are Astro Boy, Buddha, and Adolf!

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Energy Tube Chapter Two
  • Buddha Part Three: The Crystal Prince Chapter Two
  • Adolf: The Half-Aryan Chapter Four
  • Black Jack: Thieving Dog
name: Vol. 55

description:
Monarchy reigns in Black Jack: Hospital! Dr. Wanigawa rules his hospital like a tyrant, giving absolute orders that endanger a pianistís career! But when Wanigawa gives the controversial command to chop off the patientís arm, the head surgeon calls in Black Jack to find a different angle! Also included are Astro Boy, Buddha, and Dororo!

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Angel of Vietnam
  • Buddha Part Three: The Story of Yatala Chapter One
  • Dororo: Nueh
  • Black Jack: Hospital
name: Vol. 56

description:
In 1969, the 90's seemed like a far off dream, and in Astro Boy: The Summer of 1993, Tezuka imagines a future where peace is brought to Vietnam, atomic cruise liners cross the ocean, and man has set foot on Mars. Astro Boy awakens in this hypothetical 1993 to find that both mankind and robot-kind have paid a heavy price for world peace and prosperity! Also included in are Buddha, Phoenix, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Summer of 1993
  • Buddha Part Three: The Story of Yatala Chapter Two
  • Phoenix: Future Chapter Four
  • Black Jack: Quite A Tongue
name: Vol. 57

description:
In this issue's Astro Boy, Professor Ochanomizu's 63rd robot is named Chiruchiru, and today is his birthday! To celebrate the occasion, the professor gifts his robot with two masks: one happy mask and one angry mask so that Chiruchiru will have more expressions! But what will Chiruchiru do when he loses one of his masks and it falls into the wrong hands? It may not seem like much, but a robot mask can be used for evil too! Also included are Buddha, Adolf, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Robot Chiruchiru In Danger
  • Buddha Part Three: The Story of Yatala Chapter Three
  • Adolf: The Half-Aryan Chapter Five
  • Black Jack: Asking For Water
name: Vol. 58

description:
In room 66 of M University's state-of-the-art hospital, a patient is at the mercy of a mysterious disease. An incurable affliction, Monmow disease causes its victim's body to twist into sub-human shapes before suffocating to death. Determined to find a cure, the passionate Dr. Kirihito Osanai sets his sights on Doggoddale, an isolated village where the disease first appeared. Weekly Astroboy Magazine is proud to present the first chapter of Ode to Kirihito, Tezuka's 1970 medical drama! Also included in this volume are Astro Boy, Buddha, and our other favorite doctor, Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Astro's Energy Runs Out
  • Buddha Part Three: The Story of Yatala Chapter Four
  • Ode To Kirihito: Room 66
  • Black Jack: Yet False the Days
name: Vol. 59

description:
In this first installment of Astro Boy: Dr. Tenma, Tezuka reveals some of the history behind the earliest robots in Japan. As it turns out, this wasn't a very good time for robotkind! Dr. Tenma, head of the Ministry of Science in Japan, orders the mass production of Japanese robots despite protests of overcrowding from the populace. His plan? A robot slave population for the people of Japan! But will he change his mind when an unfortunate accident causes him to want a robot as his own son? Also included are Buddha, Phoenix, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Dr. Tenma Chapter One
  • Buddha Part Three: The Story of Yatala Chapter Five
  • Phoenix: Future Chapter Five
  • Black Jack: The Last Train
name: Vol. 60

description:
In Adolf, tensions are high in Kobe as the Gestapo begin to ransack Jewish homes. In the midst of the chaos, the Kamils open their doors to Elisa Gutheimer, a Jewish refugee--but are Elisa's intentions good? An anonymous phone call in the dead of night accuses Elisa of being a German spy, and Adolf is torn between trusting a beautiful girl and ensuring that his father's secret is safe. Also included are the continuations of Astro Boy and Buddha, as well as a new adventure with Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Dr. Tenma Chapter Two
  • Buddha Part Four: The Swordsman and the Drifter Chapter One
  • Adolf: The Half-Aryan Chapter Six
  • Black Jack: There Was A Valve!
name: Vol. 61

description:
The mysteries from the last installment of Astro Boy: Dr. Tenma continue! Why are there two Astro Boys? How did Astro end up in the past, anyway? And can Dr. Tenma and his wife really accept a metal robot boy as their new son? Once again, Tezuka explores the lines between real and artificial, past and present, robot and human! Also included are Buddha, Black Jack, and the first installment of Ode to Kirihito: Dead End.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: The Tragedy of Bailey
  • Buddha Part Four: The Swordsman and the Drifter Chapter Two
  • Ode To Kirihito: Dead End Chapter One
  • Black Jack: Two At the Baths
name: Vol. 62

description:
In Black Jack: Pinokoís Mystery, Pinoko discovers a letter revealing the origins of her parentage! The details are so upsetting she sets out to find the truth in the city, only to wind up lost and alone! How will she find her way back home and will Black Jack realize Pinoko knows the real story? Also included are Astro Boy, Buddha, and Phoenix!

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Astro Boy Goes To the Circus Chapter One
  • Buddha Part Four: The Swordsman and the Drifter Chapter Three
  • Phoenix: Future Chapter Six
  • Black Jack: Pinoko's Mystery
name: Vol. 63

description:
Black Jack visits a childhood friend turned mob boss in Black Jack: Imprint! Makube and Black Jack go way back, but Makubeís sudden rekindling of friendship has ulterior motives: replacing his fingerprints! Black Jack is reluctant about the situation, but the mob boss makes an offer the doctor canít refuseÖ Also included are Astro Boy, Buddha, and Adolf!

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Astro Boy Goes To the Circus Chapter Two
  • Buddha Part Four: Opponents
  • Adolf: Days of Infamy Chapter One
  • Black Jack: Imprint
name: Vol. 64

description:
Things are looking grim for the boy robot in Astro Boy: Astro Boy Goes to the Circus Chapter Three! A sudden heart attack leaves Astroís mother with a couple hours to live, but the circus master refuses to let him see her! Can Astro manage to make it in time or will his mother slip away? Also included are Buddha, Ode to Kirihito, and Black Jack!

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Astro Boy Goes To the Circus Chapter Three
  • Buddha Part Four: Showdown
  • Ode To Kirihito: Dead End Chapter Two
  • Black Jack: 99% Water
name: Vol. 65

description:
In Black Jack: The Helper, an aging surgeon senses tension in his team of medical experts! Dr. Yamadano was once a brilliant surgeon, but his eyesight is failing making it impossible to perform delicate tasks. His immoral rival is determined to have him removed as head surgeon at the expense of a patientís life! What happens when Yamadanoís team mutinies? Also included are Astro Boy, Buddha, and Phoenix!

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Living Mold From Outer Space
  • Buddha Part Four: Crisis Chapter One
  • Phoenix: Yamato Chapter One
  • Black Jack: The Helper
name: Vol. 66

description:
In this issue's Astro Boy, a group of aliens has threatened the citizens of Earth with annihilation unless they follow a single command... to treat robots as people and give them human rights! Baffled and frightened by the aliens' demands, the people of Earth scramble to figure out what to do, some countries immediately announcing equality for all robots and even pampering them. Astro seems confused by how nice everyone is suddenly being... but will it last? Also included are Buddha, Adolf, and Black Jack.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: A Declaration of Robot Rights
  • Buddha Part Four: Crisis Chapter Two
  • Adolf: Days of Infamy Chapter Two
  • Black Jack: Country Clinic
name: Vol. 67

description:
Somewhere in the mountains, in a small town who-knows-where, Black Jack encounters the mysterious legends of a ìWolf Girlî who attacks people trying to cross the border on foot! But when the Wolf Girl actually saves Black Jack from trouble and gives him shelter from the cold, how will the good doctor repay her kindness? Can he use his vast surgical knowledge to help her fit in with regular people, or will she choose a different path? Also included are Astro Boy, Buddha, and Ode to Kirihito.

Story Titles

  • Astro Boy: Astro Goes To Elementary School
  • Buddha Part Four: Deer Park
  • Ode To Kirihito: The First Symptoms
  • Black Jack: Wolf Girl
name: Vol. 68

description: Brainiac’s back…and he wants the world! What chance does the Justice League have against this technological terror reborn??
name: System Override Part 3 of 8: Malware

description: In this new collection of GREEN LANTERN #194-200, John Stewart clashes with Guy Gardner to see who will be the Green Lantern of Earth. And while Stewart battles Harbinger during the Crisis on Infinite Earths, Gardner recruits enemies of the Green Lantern Corps to stand against an evil that could destroy the entire universe - including The Shark, Hector Hammond, Sonar, Goldface and more!
name: Volume 3

description: The All-New X-Men meet the Indestructible Hulk and the Superior Spider-Man! Dr. Octopus confronts the time-displaced young X-Men, but how is he alive?! Ock's appearance gets the immediate attention of the Superior Spider-Man (who we all know is Doc Ock's mind in Spider-Man's body), and Bruce Banner helps Spidey and the young X-Men investigate the mysterious paradox - but before they learn the truth, they're shocked by the return of the believed-dead Abomination! Who is in league with these returned villains, and how can our heroes defeat them? And can the Superior Spider-Man maintain his sanity while facing his doppelganger? Plus: Steel kitchen knives meet Adamantium claws as reality-TV star Chris Cosentino spins a culinary caper featuring Wolverine! Collecting ALL-NEW X-MEN SPECIAL #1, SUPERIOR SPIDER-MAN TEAM-UP SPECIAL #1, INDESTRUCTIBLE HULK SPECIAL #1 and WOLVERINE: IN THE FLESH #1.
name: TPB

volume.name: All-New X-Men/Indestructible Hulk/Superior Spider-Man: The Arms of the Octopus

description: Jason Blood travels to Cornwall to find the spirit of Merlin and lift the curse that binds him to Etrigan, The Demon. But unraveling a centuries old curse is anything but easy, and Blood learns more about his mystical alter ego than he could have imagined. Collects the 4-issue miniseries from 1987 and issue #22 of The Demon's monthly series.
name: TPB

description: Betrayed by Etrigan and trapped in Hell, the Demon Knights must find a way to escape the clutches of Lucifer in these stories from issues #13-23. But to make their escape, someone must make the ultimate sacrifice.
name: Volume 3

description: The crossover that literally reshaped the face of Marvel's Earth is collected for the first time! When sorceress Morgan Le Fay forces the sunken continent of Atlantis back above the waves, it creates a crisis for Namor - not to mention the water-breathing Atlanteans! The Fantastic Four race to the Sub-Mariner's aid as Thor, the Inhumans and Franklin Richards' young team the Fantastic Force become ensnared in Morgan's scheme. But when the sorceress' chilling endgame comes to light, can this motley collection of heroes save the day? This is it - the catastrophe that decimated the Atlantean people, displaced Namor from Atlantis and made the Inhumans an international target! Collecting NAMOR THE SUB-MARINER #60-62, FANTASTIC FOUR: ATLANTIS RISING #1-2, FANTASTIC FORCE (1994) #8-9, FANTASTIC FOUR (1961) #401-402 and FANTASTIC FOUR UNLIMITED #11.
name: TPB

description:
Thrill to the exploits of the 31st century's greatest heroes, the original Guardians of the Galaxy! Join telekinetic Vance Astro, alien archer Yondu, flame-haired Mercurian Nikki, superstrong Jovian Charlie-27, crystalline Plutonian Martinex, and the mysterious Starhawk and his wife Aleta as they undertake a quest to find the long-lost shield of Captain America - a mission that pits them against Iron Man's twisted legacy, the marauding alien cyborgs called the Stark and the intergalactic thieves known as Force! Plus: The Guardians confront the devil's daughter, Malevolence - and battle across time alongside the Fantastic Four, Silver Surfer, Dr. Strange and the 26th century's Thor, Dargo Ktor, against the mad god known as Korvac! Collecting GUARDIANS OF THE GALAXY (1990) #1-7 and ANNUAL #1; and material from FANTASTIC FOUR ANNUAL #24, THOR ANNUAL #16 and SILVER SURFER ANNUAL #4.

Collects Guardians of the Galaxy #1-7, Guardians of the Galaxy Annual #1 and material from Fantastic Four Annual #24, Thor Annual #16 and Silver Surfer Annual #4.
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Guardians of the Galaxy By Jim Valentino

description: S.H.I.E.L.D. has the Chameleon. The Superior Spider-Man wants him. That means it's time to break into the Helicarrier! But can Spider-Man keep his secrets while facing off with the Secret Avengers - and S.H.I.E.L.D.'s newest resident, the Indestructible Hulk? When the Chameleon gets loose, it's a recipe for disaster! Plus: The Punisher and Spider-Man have never seen eye-to-eye, but this is the Superior Spider-Man! What does Frank Castle think about Spider-Man's new hard-edged attitude? Spidey has questions for the villainous Mysterio, but the Punisher has something else for him: bullets. And when Blackout targets Aunt May, the former Doc Ock's resolve is tested in a major way - and so is his patience when Stilt-Man strikes, and he must team with Spidey's old friend, Daredevil! Collecting AVENGING SPIDER-MAN #20-22, SUPERIOR SPIDER-MAN ANNUAL #1 and DAREDEVIL (2011) #22.
name: TPB

description: The X-Men's past, present and future collide in this 50th-anniversary event! Something horrible happens to the past versions of the X-Men that shakes spacetime to its core - and more X-Men arrive from the future with a message: The original five must return home! But when young Cyclops and Marvel Girl run away to stay in the present, the hunt is on! And where does the modern-day Cyclops' revolutionary faction fit in? Things get even more complicated when mysterious foes attack the Jean Grey School, and the healing-impaired Wolverine takes a mortal hit! With spacetime up for grabs, the surprise ending will change everything as the X-Men's footing in the world is drastically altered! Collecting X-MEN: BATTLE OF THE ATOM #1-2, ALL-NEW X-MEN #16-17, X-MEN (2013) #5-6, UNCANNY X-MEN (2013) #12-13 and WOLVERINE & THE X-MEN #36-37.

description: Sex, Rock & Optical Illusions is Victor Moscoso's first major, career-spanning retrospective, from his earliest poster work in 1966 to his most recent graphic experimentation. Optical Illusions contains his best posters that advertised bands playing in San Francisco's famous dance ballrooms of the time―the Avalon, the Matrix, and the Fillmoreas well as many of his Zap Comix contributions, and his solo comix work, many in Moscoso's signature color. This wide-ranging career retrospective―Moscoso's famous technique employing "vibrating colors" that he pioneered in his posters is impeccably reproduced with as much fidelity to the original as modern printing can achieve, his black-and-white and full color comix work is collected here for the first time is an intense, vibrant, and revelatory experience.
